&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bulkloader now takes the &lt;tt&gt;-ap &amp;lt;auth provider class name&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; parameter to allow a 3rd party auth provider to be used. This can be combined with the &lt;tt&gt;-u &amp;lt;username&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;-pw &amp;lt;password&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; parameters if the auth provider supports plain text credentials. In this case the auth provider must have a constructor of the form:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;public MyAuthProvider(String username, String password)
{
    ...
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
